    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-11-09T19:15:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-11-09T19:15:00-05:00" n="91"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d91">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M) Chile/284: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-09T20:15:00-04:00"
                            >November 9, 1942—8:15 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A–259. You’re a–206, October 3.<note n="8" xml:id="d91fn8">Not printed; this
                        airgram was a request for a list of products which the United States was
                        interested in purchasing.</note> Department is in receipt of a letter dated
                    November 6 from the Board of Economic Warfare giving the following list of
                    commodities available in Chile that the United States Government is interested
                    in purchasing:</p>
                <table cols="2" rend="width: 60%" rendition="#center-block" rows="6">
                    <row>
                        <cell>Copper</cell>
                        <cell>Antimony</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Manganese Ore</cell>
                        <cell>Cobalt</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Mercury</cell>
                        <cell>Gold</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Molybdenum</cell>
                        <cell>Lead</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Sheepskin Shearlings</cell>
                        <cell>Tungsten</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Nitrate of Soda</cell>
                        <cell>Zinc</cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
                <p>The Board of Economic Warfare states that any exporter desiring to offer the
                    above materials to the United States should contact Mr. Horace Graham,
                    addressing communications to him in the care of your Embassy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
